---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../config/site';
import { webPageJsonLd } from '../lib/seo';

const title = 'Terms of Service — FreeIQCheck';
const description = `Terms of Service for ${site.domain}. Rules for using our free IQ test, content, advertising, and educational quiz platform.`;
---

<LegalLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  path="/terms"
  heading="Terms of Service"
  jsonLd={[webPageJsonLd(title, description, '/terms')]}
>
  <p>
    Welcome to FreeIQCheck. These Terms of Service (&quot;Terms&quot;) govern your access to and use of <a href={site.url}>{site.url}</a>,
    including our free online IQ-style quiz, blog, guides, and related content (collectively, the &quot;Service&quot;). By accessing or
    using the Service, you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Service.
  </p>

  <h2>Eligibility</h2>
  <p>
    You must be at least 13 years old (or the minimum age required in your country to consent to online services) to use FreeIQCheck. If
    you are under 18, you should use the Service with parental or guardian permission. The quiz is for educational and entertainment
    purposes and is not directed at children under 13 for data collection purposes.
  </p>

  <h2>Educational and entertainment purpose</h2>
  <p>
    FreeIQCheck provides a <strong>free iq test online</strong> and related materials for fun, self-study, and general cognitive practice.
    Our scores are <strong>illustrative</strong> and are not clinical, medical, psychological, or employment assessments.
  </p>
  <p>
    Do not use quiz results for diagnosis, hiring, academic placement, legal proceedings, or any high-stakes decision. See our full
    <a href="/disclaimer">Disclaimer</a> for details.
  </p>

  <h2>No professional advice</h2>
  <p>
    Content on FreeIQCheck—including blog articles, guides, FAQs, and results explanations—is general information only. It does not
    constitute medical, psychological, legal, financial, or career advice. Always consult qualified professionals for matters requiring
    expert judgment.
  </p>

  <h2>Accounts and quiz use</h2>
  <p>
    No account is required to take the quiz. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of any information stored in your
    browser. Results are processed locally for display; we do not guarantee permanent storage of your attempts.
  </p>

  <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>You agree not to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Use the Service for any unlawful purpose or in violation of applicable laws</li>
    <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to systems, data, or accounts</li>
    <li>Scrape, crawl, or harvest content at scale without written permission</li>
    <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Service, servers, or networks</li>
    <li>Upload malware, spam, or harmful code</li>
    <li>Misrepresent affiliation with FreeIQCheck or impersonate others</li>
    <li>Automate quiz submissions to manipulate statistics or rankings</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We may suspend or block access for violations at our discretion.</p>

  <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
  <p>
    The Service, including design, logos, text, quiz questions, graphics, and software, is owned by FreeIQCheck or its licensors and
    protected by copyright and other intellectual property laws. You may view and use the Service for personal, non-commercial purposes.
  </p>
  <p>
    You may not copy, modify, distribute, sell, or create derivative works from our content without prior written consent, except as
    permitted by fair use or applicable law.
  </p>

  <h2>Advertising and third-party links</h2>
  <p>
    The Service may display advertisements (including through Google AdSense) and links to third-party websites. Ads and external links
    are provided for convenience. We do not endorse third-party products, services, or content and are not responsible for their
    practices. Your dealings with advertisers are solely between you and the advertiser.
  </p>
  <p>
    Third-party ad partners may use cookies and tracking technologies subject to their own policies. See our
    <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> for information on cookies and opt-out options.
  </p>

  <h2>Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
  <p>
    THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED &quot;AS IS&quot; AND &quot;AS AVAILABLE&quot; WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, WHETHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED,
    INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, TITLE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT.
  </p>
  <p>
    We do not warrant that the Service will be uninterrupted, error-free, secure, or that quiz scores are accurate, complete, or
    suitable for any particular purpose.
  </p>

  <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, FREEIQCHECK AND ITS OPERATORS, AFFILIATES, AND SUPPLIERS SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY
    INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF PROFITS, DATA, OR GOODWILL, ARISING FROM YOUR USE
    OF THE SERVICE OR RELIANCE ON QUIZ RESULTS.
  </p>
  <p>
    OUR TOTAL LIABILITY FOR ANY CLAIM ARISING FROM THESE TERMS OR THE SERVICE SHALL NOT EXCEED THE GREATER OF (A) THE AMOUNT YOU PAID US
    IN THE TWELVE MONTHS BEFORE THE CLAIM (TYPICALLY ZERO FOR FREE USERS) OR (B) ONE HUNDRED U.S. DOLLARS (USD $100).
  </p>
  <p>Some jurisdictions do not allow certain limitations; in those cases, our liability is limited to the maximum extent permitted by law.</p>

  <h2>Indemnification</h2>
  <p>
    You agree to indemnify and hold harmless FreeIQCheck from claims, damages, and expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising
    from your misuse of the Service or violation of these Terms.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to the Service and Terms</h2>
  <p>
    We may modify, suspend, or discontinue any part of the Service at any time. We may update these Terms by posting a revised version
    on this page with an updated date. Material changes will be reflected in the &quot;Last updated&quot; notice. Continued use after
    changes constitutes acceptance.
  </p>

  <h2>Governing law</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms are governed by the laws of the United States and the State in which the operator resides, without regard to conflict of
    law principles, except where mandatory consumer protection laws in your country provide otherwise.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these Terms: <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a> · <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>
  </p>
  <p>
    Related documents: <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> · <a href="/disclaimer">Disclaimer</a>
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
